*1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Full-Stack Development?*  
Full-stack dev means working on both the *frontend (client-side)* and *backend (server-side)* of a web application.

*2Ô∏è‚É£ Frontend (What Users See)*  
Languages & Tools:  
- *HTML* ‚Äì Structure  
- *CSS* ‚Äì Styling  
- *JavaScript* ‚Äì Interactivity  
- *React.js* / *Vue.js* ‚Äì Frameworks for building dynamic UIs

*3Ô∏è‚É£ Backend (Behind the Scenes)*  
Languages & Tools:  
- *Node.js*, *Python*, *PHP* ‚Äì Handle server logic  
- *Express.js*, *Django* ‚Äì Frameworks  
- *Database* ‚Äì MySQL, MongoDB, PostgreSQL

*4Ô∏è‚É£ API (Application Programming Interface)*  
- Connect frontend to backend using *REST APIs*  
- Send and receive data using JSON

*5Ô∏è‚É£ Database Basics*  
- *SQL*: Structured data (tables)  
- *NoSQL*: Flexible data (documents)

*6Ô∏è‚É£ Version Control*  
- Use *Git* and *GitHub* to manage and share code

*7Ô∏è‚É£ Hosting & Deployment*  
- Host frontend: *Vercel*, *Netlify*  
- Host backend: *Render*, *Railway*, *Heroku*

*8Ô∏è‚É£ Authentication*  
- Implement login/signup using *JWT*, *Sessions*, or *OAuth*
